A 71-year-old Johannesburg man has been shot during a robbery at his Strydom Park panelbeaters. On Friday, at around 13:00, two armed men the entered the business premises, on corner Masjien and Fabriek streets, and demanded money from an employee in the reception area, police spokesperson Colonel Lungelo Dlamini confirmed. READ | KZN cops shoot dead 9 suspects after failed robbery The suspects took around R3 000 of the company's money before walking into the workshop, where they shot the business owner. WATCH: Would-be robber shot dead outside Limpopo mall A would-be bag thief was shot and killed in the parking lot of a Polokwane mall; this after the owner of the bag gave chase, pointed a firearm at the assailant and pulled the trigger. The 71-year-old man was taken to hospital by one of his employees. The suspects are still at large. Police are investigating a case of business robbery and attempted murder.